<p>In terms of export, the report notes that ‘In January-August 2009 the exports of SMP, WMP and cheese declined slightly compared to the same period of 2008 (without refunds)’ but that at the same time ‘exports of whey powder increased by 13% and butter by 7%, with increases also of condensed milk and lactose’. The report further that notes ‘recent applications for export licences indicate a better export performance of the main commodities in the second half of 2009’, with the exception of butter.</p><table class="renderedtable" border="1" cellpadding="2" cellspacing="0">
